citation.case_name: Dunn v. County of Los Angeles

html:
357 U.S. 344

78 S.Ct. 1370

2 L.Ed.2d 1367

Myrtle May DUNN, Alvin D. Dunn and Citizens National Trust & Savings Bank of Los Angeles, Executors of the Estate of A. M. Dunn, Deceased, et al., appellants,
v.
COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES, a Body Corporate and Politic, et al.

No. 952.

Supreme Court of the United States

June 23, 1958

Mr. Henry W. Robinson, for appellants.

Mr. Harold W. Kennedy, for appellee County of Los Angeles.

Messrs. Roger J. Whiteford, John J. Wilson, Oscar John Dorwin and Ray A. Pittman, Jr., for appellee Texas Company.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed. Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari, certiorari is denied.
